### NovaLearn API — manual test flow (VS Code "REST Client" extension)
### Click "Send Request" above each block, top to bottom.

@baseUrl = https://localhost:7001/api/v1
@email = ada.lovelace@novalearn.local
@password = Str0ng!Pass

### 1. Register a new account -> 200. A verification link is written to the API console logs.
# @name register
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Ada",
  "lastName": "Lovelace",
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### 2. Login BEFORE verifying -> 403 (email_not_confirmed). This is expected.
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{ "email": "{{email}}", "password": "{{password}}" }

### 3. Verify email.
### Copy userId + token from the "[DEV EMAIL] ... Link:" line in the API console,
### then paste them here (the token is URL-encoded in the link — decode or paste raw).
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/verify-email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "PASTE-USER-ID",
  "token": "PASTE-TOKEN"
}

### 4. Login after verification -> 200. Captures the access token for step 5.
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{ "email": "{{email}}", "password": "{{password}}" }

### 5. Call a protected endpoint with the captured token -> 200.
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}

### 6. Refresh the access token (uses the refresh cookie set on login) -> 200.
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{}
